    <h2 {...{
      "id": "installing-scummvm"
    }}>{`Installing ScummVM`}</h2>
    <p>{`On a Raspberry Pi running the latest version of Raspberry OS, go to the Terminal and enter the following command into the command line:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{}}>{`sudo apt install -y scummvm
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`This command installs ScummVM.`}</p>
    <div {...{
      "className": "admonition admonition-tip alert alert--success"
    }}><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-heading"
      }}><h5 parentName="div"><span parentName="h5" {...{
            "className": "admonition-icon"
          }}><svg parentName="span" {...{
              "xmlns": "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg",
              "width": "12",
              "height": "16",
              "viewBox": "0 0 12 16"
            }}><path parentName="svg" {...{
                "fillRule": "evenodd",
                "d": "M6.5 0C3.48 0 1 2.19 1 5c0 .92.55 2.25 1 3 1.34 2.25 1.78 2.78 2 4v1h5v-1c.22-1.22.66-1.75 2-4 .45-.75 1-2.08 1-3 0-2.81-2.48-5-5.5-5zm3.64 7.48c-.25.44-.47.8-.67 1.11-.86 1.41-1.25 2.06-1.45 3.23-.02.05-.02.11-.02.17H5c0-.06 0-.13-.02-.17-.2-1.17-.59-1.83-1.45-3.23-.2-.31-.42-.67-.67-1.11C2.44 6.78 2 5.65 2 5c0-2.2 2.02-4 4.5-4 1.22 0 2.36.42 3.22 1.19C10.55 2.94 11 3.94 11 5c0 .66-.44 1.78-.86 2.48zM4 14h5c-.23 1.14-1.3 2-2.5 2s-2.27-.86-2.5-2z"
              }}></path></svg></span>{`tip`}</h5></div><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-content"
      }}><p parentName="div">{`To check that ScummVM has been installed correctly, run the following on the command line. This shows the installed version. `}</p><pre parentName="div"><code parentName="pre" {...{}}>{`scummvm -v
`}</code></pre></div></div>
    <hr></hr>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "adding-games"
    }}>{`Adding games`}</h2>
    <p>{`ScummVM needs access to the data files for each game.`}</p>
    <p>{`For games on floppies or CDs:`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">{`If the data files are accessible, transfer these to the Raspberry Pi. `}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`If the data files are not accessible, run the installer on the platform the game was designed for, and then transfer the files to the Raspberry Pi.`}</li>
    </ul>
    <p>{`For games downloaded from digital distributors such as `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "gog.com"
      }}>{`GOG.com`}</a>{`, `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://store.steampowered.com"
      }}>{`Steam`}</a>{`, or from various `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://wiki.scummvm.org/index.php?title=Where_to_get_the_games#Freeware_Games"
      }}>{`freeware`}</a>{` sources:`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">{`Run the installer and transfer the files to the Raspberry Pi, or`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`If the data files are supplied as a .zip file, extract the archive. Archives can be downloaded directly onto the Raspberry Pi, as there is no need to run the installer. `}</li>
    </ul>
    <div {...{
      "className": "admonition admonition-note alert alert--secondary"
    }}><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-heading"
      }}><h5 parentName="div"><span parentName="h5" {...{
            "className": "admonition-icon"
          }}><svg parentName="span" {...{
              "xmlns": "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg",
              "width": "14",
              "height": "16",
              "viewBox": "0 0 14 16"
            }}><path parentName="svg" {...{
                "fillRule": "evenodd",
                "d": "M6.3 5.69a.942.942 0 0 1-.28-.7c0-.28.09-.52.28-.7.19-.18.42-.28.7-.28.28 0 .52.09.7.28.18.19.28.42.28.7 0 .28-.09.52-.28.7a1 1 0 0 1-.7.3c-.28 0-.52-.11-.7-.3zM8 7.99c-.02-.25-.11-.48-.31-.69-.2-.19-.42-.3-.69-.31H6c-.27.02-.48.13-.69.31-.2.2-.3.44-.31.69h1v3c.02.27.11.5.31.69.2.2.42.31.69.31h1c.27 0 .48-.11.69-.31.2-.19.3-.42.31-.69H8V7.98v.01zM7 2.3c-3.14 0-5.7 2.54-5.7 5.68 0 3.14 2.56 5.7 5.7 5.7s5.7-2.55 5.7-5.7c0-3.15-2.56-5.69-5.7-5.69v.01zM7 .98c3.86 0 7 3.14 7 7s-3.14 7-7 7-7-3.12-7-7 3.14-7 7-7z"
              }}></path></svg></span>{`note`}</h5></div><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-content"
      }}><p parentName="div">{`If data files need to be transferred from another device onto the Raspberry Pi, there are a number of options:`}</p><ul parentName="div">
          <li parentName="ul">{`Using an external hard-drive or USB stick`}</li>
          <li parentName="ul">{`Using a `}<a parentName="li" {...{
              "href": "https://pimylifeup.com/raspberry-pi-samba/"
            }}>{`Samba server`}</a>{` or  `}<a parentName="li" {...{
              "href": "https://www.raspberrypi.org/documentation/remote-access/ftp.md"
            }}>{`FTP`}</a></li>
        </ul></div></div>
    <p>{`A comprehensive list of required data files for each game can be found on the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://wiki.scummvm.org/index.php?title=Datafiles"
      }}>{`ScummVM Wiki Datafiles`}</a>{` page.`}</p>
    <div {...{
      "className": "admonition admonition-tip alert alert--success"
    }}><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-heading"
      }}><h5 parentName="div"><span parentName="h5" {...{
            "className": "admonition-icon"
          }}><svg parentName="span" {...{
              "xmlns": "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg",
              "width": "12",
              "height": "16",
              "viewBox": "0 0 12 16"
            }}><path parentName="svg" {...{
                "fillRule": "evenodd",
                "d": "M6.5 0C3.48 0 1 2.19 1 5c0 .92.55 2.25 1 3 1.34 2.25 1.78 2.78 2 4v1h5v-1c.22-1.22.66-1.75 2-4 .45-.75 1-2.08 1-3 0-2.81-2.48-5-5.5-5zm3.64 7.48c-.25.44-.47.8-.67 1.11-.86 1.41-1.25 2.06-1.45 3.23-.02.05-.02.11-.02.17H5c0-.06 0-.13-.02-.17-.2-1.17-.59-1.83-1.45-3.23-.2-.31-.42-.67-.67-1.11C2.44 6.78 2 5.65 2 5c0-2.2 2.02-4 4.5-4 1.22 0 2.36.42 3.22 1.19C10.55 2.94 11 3.94 11 5c0 .66-.44 1.78-.86 2.48zM4 14h5c-.23 1.14-1.3 2-2.5 2s-2.27-.86-2.5-2z"
              }}></path></svg></span>{`tip`}</h5></div><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-content"
      }}><p parentName="div">{`ScummVM can run the game data files from any directory it has access to, including external media. `}</p><p parentName="div">{`For ease of use, you can create a dedicated games directory into which subdirectories containing game files can be copied. `}</p><p parentName="div">{`The resulting directory structure will look somewhat like this:`}</p><pre parentName="div"><code parentName="pre" {...{}}>{`mygames
|-- myfirstgame
|   |-- readme.txt
|   |-- firstgame.cpt
|   |-- firstgame.dnr
|   \`-- firstgame.dsk
\`-- mysecondgame
    |-- secondgame.1c
    \`-- readme.txt
`}</code></pre></div></div>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`From the Applications menu, select `}<strong parentName="li">{`Games`}{` `}{`>`}{` `}{`ScummVM`}</strong>{` to open the Launcher window.`}</li>
    </ol>
    <img alt=" " src={useBaseUrl('img/RaspberryPi/launch_scummvm_rpi.jpg')} />
    <ol {...{
      "start": 2
    }}>
      <li parentName="ol">{`In the Launcher window, click `}<strong parentName="li">{`Add Game`}</strong>{`. This opens a file browser. To add multiple games at once, hold `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`Shift`}</inlineCode>{` while clicking `}<strong parentName="li">{`Add Game`}</strong>{`.`}</li>
    </ol>
    <img alt=" " src={useBaseUrl('img/RaspberryPi/blank_launcher_rpi.jpg')} />
    <ol {...{
      "start": 3
    }}>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Use the file browser to locate the folder containing the game you wish to add. Double click on a folder to open it, and use `}<strong parentName="li">{`Go up`}</strong>{` to go back up one level. `}</li>
    </ol>
    <ol {...{
      "start": 4
    }}>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Once you have selected the folder that contains the data files, click `}<strong parentName="li">{`Choose`}</strong>{`. `}</li>
    </ol>
    <img alt=" " src={useBaseUrl('img/RaspberryPi/adding_games_rpi.jpg')} />
    <ol {...{
      "start": 5
    }}>
      <li parentName="ol">{`A dialog opens to allow configuration of various settings for the game. These can be reconfigured at any time, but for now everything should work at the default settings. Click `}<strong parentName="li">{`Ok`}</strong>{`. `}</li>
    </ol>
    <img alt=" " src={useBaseUrl('img/RaspberryPi/game_info_rpi.jpg')} />
    <ol {...{
      "start": 6
    }}>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Added games are now ready to launch!`}</li>
    </ol>
    <hr></hr>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "launching-games"
    }}>{`Launching games`}</h2>
    <p>{`There are two ways to launch a game:`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">{`From the Launcher: `}<ul parentName="li">
          <li parentName="ul">{`From the Applications menu, select `}<strong parentName="li">{`Games`}{` `}{`>`}{` `}{`ScummVM`}</strong>{` to start the Launcher. Select a game and click `}<strong parentName="li">{`Start`}</strong>{` to play. `}</li>
        </ul></li>
    </ul>
    <img class="gif" alt=" " src={useBaseUrl('img/RaspberryPi/launch_launcher.gif')} />
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">
        <p parentName="li">{`From the command line: `}</p>
        <ul parentName="li">
          <li parentName="ul">
            <p parentName="li">{`To launch a game with no additional options, run `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`scummvm`}</inlineCode>{` followed by the game id.   `}</p>
          </li>
          <li parentName="ul">
            <p parentName="li">{`To launch a game with options, run`}<inlineCode parentName="p">{` scummvm`}</inlineCode>{` , followed by any desired options, and then the game ID. For more information, see the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
                "href": "../advanced/command_line"
              }}>{`Command line options`}</a>{` page.`}</p>
          </li>
          <li parentName="ul">
            <p parentName="li">{`There are two ways to find the game id:`}</p>
            <ol parentName="li">
              <li parentName="ol">{`Go to the game-specific settings. For more information, see the `}<a parentName="li" {...{
                  "href": "#config"
                }}>{`Settings`}</a>{` section.`}</li>
              <li parentName="ol">{`Alternatively, find the default game id on the `}<a parentName="li" {...{
                  "href": "../about/supported_games"
                }}>{`Supported games`}</a>{` page. `}</li>
            </ol>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>{`In the following example, Flight of the Amazon Queen will be launched in full screen:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{}}>{`scummvm -f queen
`}</code></pre>
    <img class="gif" alt=" " src={useBaseUrl('img/RaspberryPi/launch_commandline.gif')} />
    <hr></hr>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "settings"
    }}>{`Settings `}<a id="config"></a></h2>
    <p>{`Settings can be configured from the ScummVM Launcher, or by editing the configuration file directly. `}</p>
    <p>{`To edit global settings in the Launcher, run ScummVM and click `}<strong parentName="p">{`Options`}</strong>{`. To edit game settings, choose a game and click `}<strong parentName="p">{`Edit Game`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`On the Raspberry Pi, the configuration file path is `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`~/.config/scummvm/scummvm.ini`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p>{`To edit settings directly in the config file, navigate to the file in the File Manager. If the .config directory is not visible in the Home directory, select `}<strong parentName="p">{`View`}{` `}{`>`}{` `}{`Show Hidden`}</strong>{` in the top menu. Open the config file with a text editor, and save it when the desired changes have been made. `}</p>
    <p>{`To edit the config file from the command line, type the following:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{}}>{`nano ~/.config/scummvm/scummvm.ini 
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`Use `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`Control+O`}</inlineCode>{` to save any changes. `}</p>
    <p>{`For more information about settings, see the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "../using/global_settings"
      }}>{`Global settings`}</a>{` or `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "../using/game_settings"
      }}>{`Game settings`}</a>{` page. `}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "game-saves"
    }}>{`Game saves`}</h3>
    <p>{`By default, games are saved to`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{}}>{`/home/pi/.local/share/scummvm/saves
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`The save path can be changed in the config file by setting the savepath parameter.`}</p>
    <p>{`Some engines allow saved games to be loaded directly from the command line. For more information, see the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "../advanced/command_line#list_save"
      }}>{`List save section`}</a>{` on the Command line options page. `}</p>
    </MDXLayout>;
}

;
MDXContent.isMDXComponent = true;
